OL,7,F"Clear and consistent communication
OL,8,Fwith the public is essential. People
OL,9,Fdeserve to know exactly what has
OL,10,Fhappened, how it affects them, and
OL,11,Fwhat steps are being taken to put
OL,12,Fthings right. That openness is the
OL,13,Fbest way to maintain confidence in our
OL,14,Fhealth system.
OL,16,F"I will be raising this issue directly
OL,17,Fwith the Health Minister (Mike
OL,18,FNesbitt) to ensure that the necessary
OL,19,Factions are taken swiftly and that
OL,20,Fthis type of disruption is not
OL,21,Frepeated.
